│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is an IR verification failure after loop  │
│ vectorization. The verifier reports: \"PHINode should have one entry for each │
│ predecessor of its parent basic block! %use = phi i64 [ %start2, %for.body    │
│ ]\". This indicates the loop-vectorizer mutated the CFG such that the exit    │
│ block now has a different predecessor set than before, but an existing PHI    │
│ (%use) was not updated to reflect the new predecessors. The reproducer has a  │
│ single-exit loop with a trivial loop-invariant PHI in the exit block. After   │
│ vectorization, a new predecessor (the 'middle block') is added (when no       │
│ scalar epilogue is required), but the PHI still lists the original            │
│ predecessor (which may no longer be a predecessor or is insufficient),        │
│ triggering the assertion.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe log shows the       │
│ failure occurs at the final verification in LoopVectorizePass::processLoop    │
│ right after executing the vectorization plan. No other diagnostics are        │
│ emitted. ScalarEvolution output is normal. The first transformation point     │
│ (executePlan + subsequent fix-up) completes and then verification fails at    │
│ line 10247. Thus the IR was left in an inconsistent state by earlier          │
│ transformation code, particularly inside executePlan /                        │
│ fixVectorizedLoop.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nIn executePlan, the skeleton   │
│ is created via InnerLoopVectorizer::createVectorizedLoopSkeleton, which (if a │
│ scalar epilogue is NOT required) later results in an edge from the newly      │
│ created 'middle block' directly to the loop's unique exit block (see the      │
│ diagram in comments). When this optional edge is inserted, existing PHIs in   │
│ the exit block must gain incoming values for the new predecessor.             │
│ fixVectorizedLoop only adjusts:\n- Induction variable users (fixupIVUsers)\n- │
│ Live-outs tracked in VPlan (Plan.getLiveOuts())\nIt does NOT generically      │
